---
title: Kale, Cranberry & Walnut Stuffed Squash with Parmesan & Creamy Lemon Thyme Couscous
description: Delicata squash is one of our favorite veggies for roasting—it has a sweet, buttery flavor and an edible skin that’s thin and delicate (where it gets its name!). Here, we roast the squash halves until tender, then stuff with a creamy, herby couscous filling that’s studded with dried cranberries and sautéed kale, garlic, and onion. It’s all sprinkled with Parmesan, then broiled until golden and topped with walnuts for crunch. This is the STUFF dinner dreams are made of.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/617041c8e4956756ba36e117-487f579c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/kale-cranberry-walnut-stuffed-squash-617041c8e4956756ba36e117-d60f8557.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 115 g
  sugar: 29 g
  protein: 18 g
  fiber: 12 g
  sodium: 550 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/kale-cranberry-walnut-stuffed-squash-617041c8e4956756ba36e117
cuisine: North America
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @Delicata Squash{1} lengthwise; scoop out seeds with a #spoon{} and discard.

Place squash on a #baking sheet{}; drizzle each half with @olive oil{2%tsp} and rub to evenly coat. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then arrange cut sides down.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

While squash roasts, halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}. Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}. Strip @Thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). Remove and discard any large stems from @Kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Quarter @Lemon{1}.

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat (melt 2 TBSP butter in a #large pot{} for 4 servings). Add onion; cook until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in garlic and minced thyme; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add kale and a splash of @water{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until kale is slightly wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Add @Israeli Couscous{3/4%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1} to pot with kale mixture. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain any excess liquid if necessary.

Stir in @Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, @Dried Cranberries{1%ounce}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to stuff squash.

Once squash is tender, remove from oven; heat broiler to high.

Carefully flip squash, cut sides up, and stuff with as much couscous filling as will fit, saving any remaining filling for serving. Top stuffed squash with @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}.

Broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide any remaining filling between plates. Top with stuffed squash. Sprinkle with @Walnuts{1/2%ounce}. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.